{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#5297: warnHandler not invoked prior to `app.mount()` due to null `stack` / `instance` reference",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:26:43.695446+00:00",
  "text": "warnHandler not invoked prior to `app.mount()` due to null `stack` / `instance` reference\n\n### Version\r\n3.2.27\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[jsfiddle.net](https://jsfiddle.net/smolgumball/4wvuf3ho/3/)\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n* Note logs in console\r\n* Note comment on line 11 of JS source\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n`warnHandler` be invoked for all warnings, even if app is not yet instanced / mounted.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n`warnHandler` is skipped and internal warn handler runs.\r\n\r\n### Potentially related:\r\n#4479 \r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "🔩 p2-edge-case",
    "need discussion"
  ],
